The paper discusses the use of airborne laser scanning (LiDAR) point clouds for tree segmentation in forested areas, which is a common application in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of computational approaches for big data, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the occlusion effect and the need for accurate segmentation, which are common topics in graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO).
